WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.580
I'm going to talk about L-renatamab, and these are my disclosures.

00:00:04.580 --> 00:00:09.960
And for those who are less familiar with myeloma therapies, L-renatamab is another BCMA-directed

00:00:09.960 --> 00:00:10.260
bispecific.

00:00:10.340 --> 00:00:13.880
I guess the whole section is talking about BCMA-directed bispecifics.

00:00:14.520 --> 00:00:21.100
And it was approved in August of 2023 following results of the Phase II Magnetism III or MM3

00:00:21.100 --> 00:00:25.060
trial, which showed an overall response rate of about 61%.

00:00:25.660 --> 00:00:31.400
But as time has gone on, these were the first kind of graphs that showed this plateau or

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:35.260
flattening effect that we talked about earlier, where we were seeing that these patients who'd

00:00:35.260 --> 00:00:40.280
had a median of five prior lines of therapy were having durability of remissions that

00:00:40.280 --> 00:00:41.220
was something very different.

00:00:42.180 --> 00:00:48.920
And so in that context, we have a very effective therapy that's moved into very active development.

00:00:49.140 --> 00:00:51.520
So in talking about ongoing trials, there's a lot to cover.

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:55.640
My other disclosure is that I needed Claude to help me make this.

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:57.820
This slide, because there's too many things going on.

00:00:57.900 --> 00:01:00.780
So if there's any typos, I blame Dario Amode as well.

00:01:01.900 --> 00:01:06.740
But to break this down a little bit more, in terms of ongoing trials that are most impactful

00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:11.240
to be aware of, in the relapse refractory setting, we have two different confirmatory

00:01:11.240 --> 00:01:16.580
Phase IIIs that are ongoing in the early relapse setting, the Magnetism V and Magnetism 32 trials.

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:22.000
Magnetism V is ELRA versus ELRA plus DERA versus EPD.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:25.480
I don't think EPD stands much chance, but it will be pretty interesting.

00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:29.940
We're going to see some head to head data comparing single agent BCMA bispecific versus

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:33.560
a BCMA bispecific plus a CD38 monoclonal.

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:39.300
Magnetism 32 is ELRA versus investigator's choice of EPD, PVD, KD.

00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:42.800
In the newly diagnosed setting, Magnetism VI was mentioned this morning.

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:48.020
This is ELRA/DERA/LEN versus DERA/LEN/DEX in transplant and eligible newly diagnosed

00:01:48.020 --> 00:01:49.340
patients.

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:53.900
Also mentioned was Magnetism VII, which is a randomized comparison between ELRA and lenalidomide

00:01:53.900 --> 00:01:54.900
in a maintenance setting.

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:55.420
Thank you.

00:01:55.660 --> 00:02:01.360
Two kind of interesting ongoing more sort of investigator or cooperative group sponsored

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:06.060
trials or European group sponsored trials, the ELLEN trial and FASTER are both starting

00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:11.680
to answer that question of comparison versus transplant and versus maintenance after transplant.

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:15.200
And then to talk about some combination data that's in smaller groups of patients, but

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:17.900
I think pretty informative, hopefully.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:23.940
Magnetism XX with carfilzomib and Magnetism XXX with ibertamide.

00:02:23.940 --> 00:02:25.440
